To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Idaho Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I'm looking for documents pertaining to the department's usage the COPLINK or COPLINKX software from January 1, 2018 until the date this request is processed.

1. Invoices or receipts for the purchase of any the COPLINK or COPLINKX product/service
2. Communications, internal memos or directives that mention Coplink, Face Match, or FaceMatch
3. MOU's or Information Sharing Agreements about COPLINK or COPLINKX
4. Brochures or product/service specifications about COPLINK.
5. Privacy policies,  manuals, briefings mentioning COPLINK or COPLINKX

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Dhruv Mehrotra

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Delaware Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The Notice of Program Reimbursement for the Delaware Psychiatric Center‘s Medicare cost report for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2019.  Also, please provide the Notice of Program Reimbursement for each amended cost report for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2019, if the cost report was amended.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jonathan Rudenberg, a citizen of Delaware, in coordination with Mark Jeziorski.
